 you might not want to put off investing any longer, because it takes time to experience the effect. Here’s why... Let's say you invested $20 a week. After 20 years, your $20,800 investment would be worth over $34,000. (Assuming a 5% compound annual return)Why do you need my Social Security number?The Patriot Act requires all financial institutions to obtain, verify, and record information that identifies each person opening an account. We also require your Social Security number to issue you a tax reporting form at the end of the year. Your Social Security number is only used to verify your identity. Stash does not perform a credit check.Is the money invested in my Stash Account protected?Your investments with Stash are protected by the Securities Investor Protection Corporation (SIPC). All holdings and cash are held at APEX Clearing Corp. For more information on SIPC insurance, please visit www.sipc.org.

Master Investment Portfolio - Active Stock Master Portfolio: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 1:42 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Master Investment Portfolio - Active Stock Master Portfolio



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Master Investment Portfolio - Active Stock Master Portfolio is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched by BlackRock, Inc. It is managed by BlackRock Fund Advisors. The fund invests in public equity markets of the United States. It invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in dividend paying, growth and value stocks of large cap and mid cap companies having markets capitalization of $2 billion or more or within the range of the Russell 1000 Index. It employs a combination of quantitative and fundamental analysis with bottom up stock picking approach by focusing on factors such as earnings, cash flows, company's financial condition, and earnings re...
Master Investment Portfolio - Active Stock Master Portfolio is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched by BlackRock, Inc. It is managed by BlackRock Fund Advisors. The fund invests in public equity markets of the United States. It invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in dividend paying, growth and value stocks of large cap and mid cap companies having markets capitalization of $2 billion or more or within the range of the Russell 1000 Index. It employs a combination of quantitative and fundamental analysis with bottom up stock picking approach by focusing on factors such as earnings, cash flows, company's financial condition, and earnings reports, and management to create its portfolio. The fund employs proprietary research to create its portfolio. Master Investment Portfolio - Active Stock Master Portfolio was formed on March 15, 2004 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


400 Howard StreetSan Francisco, CA 94105United StatesFounded in 2004



Phone: 415-670-2000

Fax: 415-618-5014








