Master portfolios - Build your own investment portfolio

What are Master Portfolios?

Master Portfolios are designed to help you get started with investing
There are five example portfolios depending on your aims and attitude to risk
The underlying funds are selected by our investment team and run by the best fund managers in their field
You can tailor each portfolio by changing the percentage invested in each fund according to your own preferences

How do Master Portfolios work?
The portfolios are designed as a starting point, and while each fund is professionally managed, the overall responsibility for selecting and managing the portfolio rests with you. We will send you updates with our latest views on each of the component funds to help you with this.
The portfolios are not personal advice - if you're unsure whether an investment is right for you, contact us for financial advice. All investments fall as well as rise in value - you could get back less than you invest. For this reason we suggest investing for a minimum of five years.
Choose your portfolio style

Adventurous
Medium risk
Conservative
Investing for children
Regular income



			This aggressive portfolio aims to generate a high level of capital growth by focusing on higher-risk areas like emerging markets and smaller companies.
		

			This medium-risk portfolio aims for a reasonable return with less volatility than more aggressive options.
		

			This defensive portfolio aims for modest growth whilst minimising volatility, though it can still fall in value.
		

			Children usually have a long investment horizon, so this portfolio focuses on higher-risk areas with greater growth potential.
		

			This income portfolio is designed to produce a good level of income with the potential to grow and keep pace with inflation.
		
How much do you want to invest?


Lump sum (min £500): £


Monthly amount (min £125): £


Calculate



We amend the number of funds according to the amount you want to invest. This helps to ensure that you have a well-diversified portfolio. Please note, this has not been tailored to your individual circumstances.


Portfolio suggestion

The following four funds have been selected by our award-winning research team. They dovetail well together to provide a ready-made, diversified portfolio with exciting growth potential.
You can invest in the portfolio as it stands, but using the sliders you can tailor it to suit your needs. If you want to add additional funds, you can leave a cash weighting which can be invested as you wish.
Please note that the minimum investment into each fund is £100 lump sum or £25 per month.


