For My Future


                    Master Investment Plan
                












































Master Investment Plan













                    
            Professionally managed investment portfolio to give you greater upside potential in achieving your financial goals.
        

Whatever your financial goal is, your first step is to invest. Master Investment Plan is specially designed to manage your investment by means of units hold. You may take advantage of our professional investment expertise in a portfolio of diversified investments. 




Note: This is an insurance product that is tied to the performance of its underlying assets and is NOT a pure investment product like unit trusts.
    












            Why should I choose this plan?
        






Here are seven reasons to buy this plan:
High Growth Potential and Yields
The success of Master Investment Plan is linked to the different types of investments, including shares bought on Bursa Malaysia, fixed income securities such as bonds, cash deposits and financial investments. This means that the Master Investment Plan, will, over the long term, benefit from any gains made in the stock market as well as from high interest rates earned from bonds and cash deposits. The best time to buy Master Investment Plan is when the stock market is low.

Investment Diversification
Master Investment Plan invests in a large and diversified portfolio of investments on behalf of many investors. With large amounts to manage, Master Investment Plan is able to invest in many different shares as well as place funds in guaranteed areas of return such as cash and bonds. This diversification allows all investors in Master Investment Plan, both large and small, to benefit from broad-based and diversified investments. Diversification helps protect your investment from sudden downturns in individual shareholdings whilst providing consistent returns when markets are rising.

Tax Advantages
Your Master Investment Plan is classified as a ‘Single Premium Investment-Linked Life Insurance Policy’. This means that under current arrangements, when you cash in part or all of your plan in the future, the proceeds are treated in the same way as other Life Insurance policies and is tax-free. This makes Master Investment Plan an ideal investment vehicle for long term savings, especially if you would like to benefit from additional tax-free cash drawings from your Master Investment Plan during retirement.

Professional Investment Management
No longer do you have to worry about what to buy, or when. Zurich’s professional investment management team in Malaysia has over 30 years’ experience in money management, buying and selling stocks and shares, bonds and placing funds in areas which secure the best rates of return. In addition, the team can tap into the diverse expertise and experience of investment professionals working for Zurich around the globe. This has resulted in thousands of investors making consistently good returns as policyholders of Zurich. Your Master Investment Plan provides professional money management around the clock, freeing you to do the things you want to do, and providing you with peace of mind.

Choice of Funds
Master Investment Plan offers a selection of funds to choose from under one plan to suit your individual investment requirements.

Transfer/Switch Facility
Master Investment Plan allows you to switch your investments from one fund to another whenever you need, giving you ultimate control over your investment exposure.

Death or Total and Permanent Disability (TPD) Benefit
Master Investment Plan will pay out a guaranteed Death or Total and Permanent Disability Benefit, in the unlikely event of something happening to you. This makes Master Investment Plan an ideal planning vehicle when investing for your future, your loved ones as well as yourself.










            Who is eligible for this plan?
        
















FOR POLICYHOLDER
Minimum: 18 years old
            Maximum: No limit
            


FOR INSURED
Minimum: 30 days
            Maximum: 70 years old
            














